I went to my sisters house this morning because even at 27 I still need hand holding when I am about to do something scary. Today was the day. I sent out queries to my top two agents and I am going to have 10 sent out by tomorrow evening. I've come to a point with my story where I can't move forward without someone with more experience and I'm so over it that what do I have to lose if it gets rejected? I'm ready to either take the next step or move on to the next story. This is probably the point I had to get to if I was going to put myself out there. Whatever happens is meant to be. I trust the unfolding of my story. 🙏🏻

do not ruin your #content in order to try and #rank for more #keywords

even that single #ranking #keyword will give enough attention and exposure to your #website in the long run, potential #customers just need to find your website

once they know you have what they are interested in they will come to you

and even if its one keyword, make it worth 10 keywords by adding most of your products or information in that page

for e.g. a fruit seller has mango fruit item ranking, in that case he should put #descriptions of all other fruits in that page so people can see every single fruit he is selling and even without doing so, if someone comes to the #site #searching for the #query of mango, she/he will come to know about other fruits automatically upon the visit as that single keyword has OPENED THE DOOR TO EVERYTHING YOUR WEBSITE IS REPRESENTING, in this example every other fruit will be explored and also once the #buyer is happy, they are likely to try other fruits

thus even a single keyword is the key to grand opportunity, power of #SEO

You must focus on making you house as attractive as possible to stand a chance of selling it successfully on your own. It should be perfectly clean inside and out, with flawlessly groomed landscaping and floors. A home inspection can help you find out what renovations you need to complete. After that, you need to deep-clean your home which encompasses all aspects of cleaning from the bathroom, bedroom and living room cleaning to garage, basement and backyard cleaning. 
Remember that potential home buyers aren’t there to admire your personal tastes and preferences but to see themselves in your home.
